<div id="review_20839405" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/20839405" />
    <a title="Maria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/739304-maria"><img alt="Maria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1207018071p2/739304.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/20839405?book_show_action=true">Apr 23, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria" href="/user/show/739304-maria">Maria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780671776138" href="/book/show/358663.Plain_Truth">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">no one. </span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer20839405" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17330593951220229997">I have read many of Jodi Picoult&apos;s books and I have to say this one sucked. I was not intrigued by Katie, I was annoyed and exasperated with her. <br/><br/>The dialogue was cheesy in many areas, and the whole thing with Hannah’s ghost was just stupid. I mean, it really does seem that the only reason the ghost was added was so that the author could explain Katie’s attraction to Adam. Oh look, he’s a ghost hunter and I see a ghost—hmmm, it must be meant to be: we should have sex. Blah.<br/><br/>I’m really disappointe</span>
  <span id="freeText17330593951220229997" style="display:none">I have read many of Jodi Picoult's books and I have to say this one sucked. I was not intrigued by Katie, I was annoyed and exasperated with her. <br /><br />The dialogue was cheesy in many areas, and the whole thing with Hannah’s ghost was just stupid. I mean, it really does seem that the only reason the ghost was added was so that the author could explain Katie’s attraction to Adam. Oh look, he’s a ghost hunter and I see a ghost—hmmm, it must be meant to be: we should have sex. Blah.<br /><br />I’m really disappointed because I tend to enjoy most of Picoult’s novels. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17330593951220229997" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


