<div id="review_56668370" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/56668370" />
    <a title="Thomas" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2018505-thomas"><img alt="Thomas" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1567953607p2/2018505.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/56668370?book_show_action=true">May 19, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Thomas" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Thomas" href="/user/show/2018505-thomas">Thomas</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2018505-thomas?shelf=realistic-fiction">realistic-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2018505-thomas?shelf=five-stars">five-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2018505-thomas?shelf=adult-fiction">adult-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer56668370" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12137145110735192308">&quot;Plain Truth&quot; is about Ellie Hathaway, a lawyer from Pennsylvania who comes to an Amish community to defend Katie, an eighteen year old accused of murdering her own newborn child. During the bail process of Katie&apos;s trial, Ellie becomes her bail official person, or the person that must stay with Katie always so she can stay at her farm home. While Ellie stays with Katie, she learns the ways of the Amish community and their practices, their ways of life, and their obvious truth. And everything get</span>
  <span id="freeText12137145110735192308" style="display:none">"Plain Truth" is about Ellie Hathaway, a lawyer from Pennsylvania who comes to an Amish community to defend Katie, an eighteen year old accused of murdering her own newborn child. During the bail process of Katie's trial, Ellie becomes her bail official person, or the person that must stay with Katie always so she can stay at her farm home. While Ellie stays with Katie, she learns the ways of the Amish community and their practices, their ways of life, and their obvious truth. And everything gets more complicated when a man from Ellie's past decides to reenter her life to assist in Katie's trial. Ellie builds a strong bond with Katie while trying to figure out what really happened on the night of the allegated murder, and also searches deep inside of herself to figure out what she really wants the most in her life.<br /><br />I really do love Jodi Picoult's writing. Her characters are so realistic and throughout the story I felt like I really, personally knew them. Although she always writes about hot button topics, she accurately described the Amish community and how they lived, which made me feel privileged to be able to witness an entire book through their lives, even if it is fiction. Her writing is also mesmerizing, if I wasn't so busy this week I probably would've finished this book in a couple of days. The only thing I didn't love about this book was the twist at the end, although it helps wrap up the plot, it makes you question what message Picoult has been trying to establish through the entire nvoel. I still would give it five stars, read it!</span>
  <a data-text-id="12137145110735192308" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

